.SH "NAME"
.LP
checkpoint-node - Checkpoint specified node.
.SH "SYNTAX"
.LP
\fBcheckpoint-node --node=\fINODENAME\fB
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.LP
The checkpoint-node tool takes a checkpoint of the given node which can then be used to revert the node back to should the need arise.  

NOTE: Both the node adapter and the storage adapter for the given node must support this operation.
.LP
.SH "OPTIONS"
.LP
.TP
\fB--node=\fINODENAME\fB
Name of node to checkpoint
.LP
